Gerhard Wolf - Wikipedia|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gerhard_Wolf|"Gerhard Wolf (1886 [sic]–1962). German consul, born at Dresden—subsequently twinned with the city of Florence—played a decisive role in the salvation of the Ponte Vecchio (1944) from the barbarism of the Second World War and was instrumental in rescuing political prisoners and Jews from persecution at the  ...    Gerhard Wolf (12 August 1896 – 23 March 1971) was a German diplomat who served as consul in  ...    Between 1940 and 1944, Wolf was the German consul in Florence. After the German occupation of Italy in  ...    saved many artworks from being spirited off to Germany. He also prevented the Ponte Vecchio from being  ...    In 1955, Wolf was made an honorary citizen of Florence. Ten years after his retirement, he died in Munich. In 2007, a marble plaque in his honour was unveiled on the Ponte Vecchio by the acting mayor of Dresden. 1945 Diplomatic passport issued to consul Gerhard Wolf.  ## Further reading - Tutaev, David. Der Konsul von
